==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Daphnin
<hw>Daph"nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>daphnine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A dark
green bitter resin extracted from the mezereon (<spn>Daphne
mezereum</spn>) and regarded as the essential principle of the
plant.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A white, crystalline,
bitter substance, regarded as a glucoside, and extracted from
<spn>Daphne mezereum</spn> and <spn>Daphne alpina</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Daphnomancy</ent>⟦br⟧
